storyInfo: Breaking away from the young Inquisitor, Skadi runs into another, more senior Inquisitor, and after the two engage in a melee, Skadi flees, bloodied. Before long, the monsters from the sea have found her.

attributes.content: High Inquisitor!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Stand down. You're no adversary for her.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: But I...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Stand down.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: By your order!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: Ten meters separate Skadi from the person before her, as they stare face to face.

attributes.content: You. You're very strong.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You should not have set foot in this city.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'm already here.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Violate the rules, and you must pay the price.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: I can't care about that much.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You will remain here.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: I don't want to fight with you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hmph. Wicked Ægir, you're surely frightened! Now that the High Inquisitor is here, you absolutely cannot run.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But, if this is necessary—
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: (Ægirian) I will take you down.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Such speed! So much faster than her prior hand-to-hand bout with me!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: With speed like that, I could hardly even hope to touch her hemline... Just how much more was she still hiding?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: Before she collides with the High Inquisitor, Skadi steps back.
As if a fish tossed in the air by the ocean waves, she leaps high, and lands on a dilapidated roof.

The High Inquisitor follows in mirror fashion. Their figures crash together, pull apart, then crash again. The city can barely endure such a clash, torn apart as it is, and fragments of buildings are building up rapidly on the street.

attributes.content: Her attack and evasion are becoming more and more rapid, as are my instructor's. I almost can't keep up now.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Was I really... still this lacking?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: No, this won't do. That's an Ægir. Of course I cannot lose to an Ægir.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yet this Ægir seems, somehow, to be using that case of hers as a weapon... Just what is that made of?! Why is it so tough?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But my instructor isn't using the handcannon. If he was... wouldn't we have her seized in a blink? It'd blow this entire street into slag.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Is that... simply an Ægir, however? Her appearance is nothing at all like those monsters...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: She's using... some form of Arts, is it? I can't quite tell. And our lamp... cannot inhibit her power whatsoever.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: —This Ægir has too many secrets kept with her.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: The shaking throughout the whole street gradually ceases. Amidst the shards and smoke, the senior Inquisitor appears again.

attributes.content: High Inquisitor! You're victorious. I knew no one could ever sway you by even a hair.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Er, where's that Ægir?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Fled.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: What? That... how?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: She is injured, and cannot run far.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'll search for her—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You cannot overcome her.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Ahem... But we absolutely cannot allow her sort to run free along the coast!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Direction suggests she may have made for the citizens' assembly area. She's likely mixed in with the crowd, and has accomplices among the citizens aiding her. I'll search the houses for her one by one.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: If you believe this is right, then go.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Understood—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: High Inquisitor, was she the one who brought anomaly upon this city?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I had you go and see. What was it you saw?
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: The behavior of the locals is highly abnormal. It's as if they live every day in an unwoken state. They act, yet not to complete anything. When they eat, it's not even to fill their stomachs.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They're entering the sea, and they don't even consider it suicide.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Did you put a stop to them?
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yes. This is evidently wrong, after all.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: What we are concerned with is the results. If you believe your corrections can have right results, then go do so.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Right results...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: If they cannot, then you must make some choices.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Inquisitor—with your own two eyes, your blade, you must stare down the greatest menaces to Iberia.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yes, sir!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The greatest menace to Iberia... is those monsters presently climbing ashore.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Could it be? These people who head into the ocean have some relation to these monsters?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Yes... they are surely related.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I remember you once taught that abnormality often takes more than a single form. Between all these terrible visions, there must be connections.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: To address an issue—you must first see clearly where that issue lies.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: I—I know!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: —It's those Ægirs hidden in the darkness, conspiring everything!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They're hidden ashore, concealed in the minor loopholes of our laws, rotting our cities' skin and flesh, destabilizing our fellows' wills, attempting to corrode our country's muscle and bone.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Before their plot prevails, before it drags this city into the abyss of despair—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: We must—find them—and wipe them out!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Singer... singer? Are you in here?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I've been searching for you forever. The Inquisitors won't know about this place. There are too many empty houses here, and come night, searching will be awfully hard.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I know... I'm sure you want to avoid us. That the farther you stay from where we live, the better.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Finding you here definitely wasn't easy... phew... it's so close to the coast.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Is this the sound of the waves? I never knew it was so loud. And... I can hear breathing now.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Singer, what are you doing in here? Your breathing's become quite different.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're all in danger.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What are you talking a... um, what's—are you hurt?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I'm bleeding. Get away!
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Thinking of leaving? It won't be that easy.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: The Inquisitor?! Did you follow me the whole way...? I—I didn't realize.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I could hardly let a commoner notice me. *cough* Of course, even if I don't tail you, I'd still have methods of finding this place!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You again.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What's wrong? Scared now?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Earlier—Ahem—I concede, I was negligent for a moment, and narrowly let you escape.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: But now, Ægir, I'll definitely have you caught!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: B—But, she's already hurt—
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Hmm? Are you certain about getting in my way, so as to protect a dangerous Ægir, citizen? If so, you'll become a criminal, the same as her!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You and all the others are unalike. At the very least, your eyes show fear.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Until now, you have not yet done wrong. Out of the way! I don't want to have to sort you out with my blade.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It's not the time—
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: It's not what time? Are... Are you scorning me? You think I have absolutely no way to seize you?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hmph. Certainly, I may not be the High Inquisitor. But I've already made my preparations.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I will deal with you, no matter the cost to me!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.text: Sword still unsheathed, Skadi proceeds to grasp the Inquisitor

attributes.content: What—What is the meaning of this?
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Don't make noise.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Unhand me, you Ægir reprobate! You'd better not think I can't employ my sword with a hand pinned, and I still have the handcannon—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Keep it down. They'll hear you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Ngh-ghhh... I can't move... my other hand either...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Um, can either of you hear something?
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I heard... sticky things, rubbing along the floor... so, so many... and the sound was right outside.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What... is that? It's not the work of any of us. I've never heard it before...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: They're closing in.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Their numbers are growing.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: What is causing it? The people of this place, or that woman and her companion?
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Ten of them—
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Twenty of them.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: —Still growing, still advancing. Something is leading them to clamber ashore, and spill into the city.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: And their course stems from—
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: The chapel.
attributes.name: High Inquisitor

attributes.content: Hm? They are very excited.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Are you sure you should be petting these things so?
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: Pay mind to the words you use. They are not 'things' of any sort. They are already a part of this expanse of ocean. They have become the heirs born of the sea, and are much purer than you are.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Ah... the news on the tide has already arrived. Tonight will be yet another special one.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: They have surely smelt the scent. When bloodkin join them, they become so spirited, so agitated, that they even wish to emerge from the sea, and give their welcome on land.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: It is very normal. We all love our own brothers and sisters.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Do you truly treat them as your own brothers?
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: Why not, I ask? At times of necessity, I am willing to address those of land, those who cannot help but still walk on two legs, as my brothers too.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: If you did not hold the most dirtied, mixed blood within you, then one day, you may also possess this chance.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Oh? What a crying shame.
attributes.name: Gladiia

attributes.content: (He touches the seawater.)
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Fascinating. This evening... they seem to be especially vigorous. Perhaps because so many old friends have come as guests to their home.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: Are you not curious? Wondering just what is happening upon the surface.
attributes.name: Bishop

attributes.content: ...Loud.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: So loud. I cannot sleep.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Stuff your head in your quilt.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: I cannot hear.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: I cannot see.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: Ngh... So hungry...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: So hungry.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant C

attributes.content: So hungry.
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant D

attributes.content: Sheetmetal...
attributes.name: Male Inhabitant B

attributes.content: Ah!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Uwargh-wah-hh—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They're here.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What—What are these horrendous things?! Black... flowers? Or fish? Why do they move? How disgusting, eugh...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It couldn't be... That's not right, this doesn't make sense!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: They're knocking on the windows! Are they... do they want to enter?!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: W—We cannot let them!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Close the windows shut—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: It's pointless. The windows here are all broken. Look at the top, it's full of cracks...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: —They're reaching in!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Uwargh, it's still moving! Is this tiny chunk writhing on the floor trying to force its way to us?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Even supposing it's one of those things... nothing gives it the right to be so difficult!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: So very many... there's still so many outside.
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Why can I not cut them down?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: My lamp... no, the lamp would be of no use against them.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I only have enough ammunition for one more round.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I—Inquisitor?!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Freeze! In a moment, I'll fire, and you two run for the interior. The ruins ought to be a little sturdier than these worn-out windows.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Your hand is trembling...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Holy scriptures... lend me strength.
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I—I do not fear them!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'll head out right away, kill as many as I can, and I should be able to hold a wave back. You must run with haste...
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: You, take her and hide inside.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What? What are you spouting?! Have you not seen? I can't cope with—this many! They're nigh coming in already. There's no difference between the inside and outside!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Remember, as far from doors and windows as possible.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: You utterly don't listen to people when they tell you—
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: I'll go out. Draw them away.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: What?!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Singer, you can't go outside either...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: You're very strong, stronger than anyone I've seen before, but you're hurt! And these odd things—there's—there's so many of them!
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: Inquisitor, don't—don't leave either...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: What if we all hide together? I—I know there's a cupboard in here, and the door still closes. It's in the back. If all three of us squeeze, we should hopefully...
attributes.name: Anita

attributes.content: I have to go out. Only this way, will you survive.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Hey! Ægir, even if you want to play the hero, this isn't your place to!
attributes.name: Inquisitor

attributes.content: Listen well. This is genuinely nothing to do with you.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Because—they're here looking for me.
attributes.name: Skadi

attributes.content: Skadi pushes open the door.
A long-lost scent following the sea breeze bores into the brain's tissue, creatures never of dry land pack densely into the streets.
They bubble up and down, spitting, contracting, imitating rot and growth in their actions, the shore of civilization falling to their sinister bodies.
